---
title: Samosa-Inspired Turkey and Rice with Mango Chutney and Fresh Salad
description: This meal is inspired by samosas, the popular Indian street snack. Ground turkey is cooked with a fragrant spice mix, peas and potatoes, before being draped over fragrant and steamed butter rice. Earthy and spice-filled Indian flavours really do come alive in this recipe!

Ingredients: Ground turkey • Red potato • Basmati rice • Yellow onion • Roma tomatoes • Mango chutney (sugars (sugar, mango puree), mango, concentrated vinegar, salt, garlic powder, spices, xanthan gum, ascorbic acid, beta carotene, sodium benzoate, potassium sorbate) • Spring mix (lolla rosa multi-leaf lettuce, red flash red oak lettuce, red leaf multi-leaf lettuce, green oak lettuce, bally hoo tango lettuce) • Green peas • Rice vinegar (rice vinegar, water, sugar, salt, potassium metabisulphite) (sulphites) • Indian spice blend (spices, coriander, garlic powder, salt, chili powder, oleoresin paprika, canola oil, silicon dioxide) • Beef broth concentrate (beef stock, sugars (maltodextrin, sugar), beef flavor (flavoring, water, salt, dried beef stock, beef stock, yeast extract, xanthan gum, glutamic acid, tricalcium phosphate), beef fat, salt, yeast extract, xanthan gum).
